            <h2 class="section-title">Stouffville Appliance Repair FAQ: Your Questions Answered</h2>

            <div class="faq-grid">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
                        <span>Do you service rural properties and horse farms in Stouffville?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p><strong>Yes! Rural properties are our specialty.</strong> We service horse farms throughout Ballantrae and rural Stouffville with commercial-grade laundry equipment (large-capacity washers for barn use), barn refrigerators/freezers, and heavy-duty appliances. Same-day service commitment for remote locations. We stock parts for Speed Queen, Maytag Commercial, and other heavy-duty brands. No extra travel fees within Stouffville boundaries. Call before 2 PM for same-day service at <a href="tel:437-747-6737" style="color: #2196F3; text-decoration: underline;">437-747-6737</a>.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
                        <span>Can you repair commercial-grade laundry equipment for equestrian facilities?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p><strong>Absolutely! Equestrian laundry is our specialty.</strong> Stouffville's thriving horse community requires heavy-duty solutions. We repair large-capacity washers (5.0+ cu ft), commercial-grade dryers, stacked units, and residential commercial models from Speed Queen, Maytag Commercial, and Whirlpool. We understand the unique demands of horse blankets (15-20 lbs wet), saddle pads, and continuous barn laundry cycles. Stock reinforced bearings, heavy-duty transmissions, and commercial motors. Cost: $250-$500 depending on equipment. Free consultation on best appliances for equestrian use.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
                        <span>What appliances handle Stouffville's well water best?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p><strong>Well water requires specific appliance choices and maintenance.</strong> Best performers: <strong>Whirlpool/Maytag</strong> with stainless steel tubs (resist mineral staining), <strong>GE</strong> with self-cleaning filter systems, <strong>Bosch/Miele</strong> with European hard-water engineering. Essential additions: inline sediment filters (5-20 micron), water softener coordination, and regular descaling maintenance. We provide free water quality assessment with every service call, recommend optimal settings for your water hardness (typically 450+ mg/L in rural Stouffville), and install protective filtration. Prevention is key: water softener systems ($1,200-2,000) prevent 90% of damage.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
                        <span>Are same-day repairs guaranteed for remote Ballantrae locations?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p><strong>Yes - we commit to same-day service for all Stouffville areas including remote Ballantrae!</strong> Call before 2 PM for same-day guarantee. We maintain comprehensive parts inventory (top 200 components for all major brands) in service vehicles to minimize return trips. Travel time to Ballantrae: 15-20 minutes from Historic Downtown. <strong>No rural surcharges</strong> within Stouffville boundaries. We understand the challenges of remote properties and the importance of getting it right the first time. Emergency 24/7 service available (+$75-150 surcharge). Contact us at <a href="tel:437-747-6737" style="color: #2196F3; text-decoration: underline;">437-747-6737</a>.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
                        <span>Do you service outdoor kitchens and wine cellars in country estates?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p><strong>Yes! Luxury estate appliances are our specialty.</strong> Stouffville's country estates require premium service. We repair: <strong>Sub-Zero</strong> wine refrigerators (all models including dual-zone), <strong>Wolf</strong> outdoor grills and ranges, <strong>Viking</strong> professional equipment, <strong>Miele</strong> wine coolers and steam ovens, outdoor-rated refrigerators, weatherproof ice makers, and high-end built-in appliances. Manufacturer certifications maintained. We use brand-specific diagnostic tools, stock premium OEM parts, and understand climate control requirements for wine storage. Estate maintenance programs available. Cost: $300-$600 depending on brand and complexity.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
                        <span>Can you coordinate with builders in new Legacy/Parkwoods subdivisions?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p><strong>Yes - new subdivision support is part of our service!</strong> Legacy and Parkwoods rapid development creates unique challenges. We work directly with builders, coordinate Tarion warranty claims, provide emergency repairs when warranty service is delayed (common 7-14 day delays), and stock parts for builder-grade brands (Samsung, LG, Frigidaire budget lines). We understand authorization processes, paperwork requirements, and builder warranty limitations. Honest assessments: we'll tell you if builder-grade appliances are worth repairing vs. upgrading. Young family friendly: flexible scheduling for working parents, same-day service to minimize disruption. Cost: $180-$350 for most builder-grade repairs.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
                        <span>Do you stock parts for high-end brands common in Stouffville homes?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p><strong>Yes! Premium brand parts are in our inventory.</strong> Stouffville's country estates and Historic Downtown heritage homes feature luxury appliances. We maintain stock for: <strong>Sub-Zero</strong> (sealed system components, electronic controls), <strong>Wolf</strong> (igniters, valves, burner assemblies), <strong>Miele</strong> (circulation pumps, electronic boards), <strong>Bosch</strong> (European metric fittings), <strong>Viking</strong> (professional range components), and <strong>Thermador</strong> (built-in parts). For specialty items not in stock, we offer expedited ordering (24-48 hours) with manufacturer direct relationships. All parts are genuine OEM, not aftermarket substitutes. Premium parts priced at manufacturer MSRP - transparent pricing.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-expanded="false">
                        <span>Can you help with water softener integration for appliances?</span>
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p><strong>Yes - water softener coordination is essential for Stouffville well water!</strong> We provide: water quality assessment (test hardness, iron, manganese, sediment), appliance settings optimization for your specific water hardness (typically 450+ mg/L in rural areas), inline sediment filter installation (5-20 micron protection), water softener system coordination (we work with your existing system or recommend installation), and descaling maintenance for hard water damage. <strong>Prevention is key:</strong> Properly configured water softener systems ($1,200-2,000 installed by plumbing specialists) prevent 90% of future appliance damage. We coordinate with local plumbers for complete solutions. Every service call includes free water quality assessment.</p>
                    </div>
